Hãy học và ghi nhớ đoạn sau giúp tôi
10 Habits of People With Extremely High IQ 
If you do even three of these 10 things, your IQ is probably higher than you think. These aren't study habits or test scores. They're unconscious patterns that reveal how your brain actually works. One, they question everything. Smart people rarely accept things at face value. They ask, "Why is it like that?" even about simple things.
They don't argue to win, they argue to understand. This habit builds critical thinking, not cynicism. It's why they notice flaws in systems that most people just accept. Two, they talk less, think more. While most people rush to speak, high IQ individuals pause. They think before reacting, not because they're slow, but because they're filtering.
That silence isn't shyness, it's mental editing. Research shows intelligent people often verbalize internally before they speak. That's why their words hit deeper. Three, they obsess over patterns. They're natural pattern hunters in behavior, conversations, or data. Their brain automatically looks for connections others miss.
That's why they can predict outcomes before they happen. It's not magic, it's just pattern sensitivity. Four, they think in layers, not circles. Yes, they overthink, but not in circles. They think in layers. They imagine every outcome, fix every flaw, then simplify it all down. It's like mental chess, 10 moves ahead.
This strategic overthinking is a sign of analytical depth, not anxiety. Five, they read, but differently. They don't read just to finish a book, they read to absorb models of thinking. That's why they jump between topics, philosophy today, coding tomorrow. Their curiosity isn't random, it's cross-training for the brain. High IQ people feed on mental variety, not just volume.
Six, they can sit in silence. Most people hate silence because it forces self-reflection, but the intelligent crave it. That's where their mind organizes chaos. That quiet time is how they generate insights that seem to come out of nowhere. They're not antisocial, they're processing.
Seven, they brutally honest with themselves. They don't lie to themselves to feel better. If they fail, they say, "That's on me." This level of self-awareness is rare. It's what keeps them improving, because you can't fix what you refuse to see. Eight, they love solving problems nobody asked them to solve. They see inefficiency and instantly want to optimize it.
That's why they automate, create systems, or invent shortcuts no one else noticed. It's not arrogance, it's cognitive play. For them, solving problems is fun. Nine, they manage energy, not time. While most people schedule hours, they schedule focus. They know their mental peaks and protect them. Morning, deep work. Afternoon, creative chaos.
They don't force productivity, they flow with their cognitive rhythm. 10, they know how to sound normal. Here's the twist, truly intelligent people blend in. They simplify complex ideas so others understand. That's emotional intelligence meeting raw intellect. Because real genius isn't about sounding smart, it's about making others feel smart.
So, if you relate to even a few of these, don't downplay it. You don't have to win awards to be intelligent, your habits already reveal it. The question isn't, "How smart are you?" It's, "How well are you using the mind you already have?" Which one of these habits do you recognize in yourself? Drop the number in the comments.
Let's see how many of us think this way.